{{Infobox protected area | name = Deogyusan National Park | alt_name = 덕유산국립공원, 德裕山國立公園 | iucn_category = V | photo = Deogyusan from Hyangjeok Peak.jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Mountain [[Deogyusan]], viewed from Hyangjeok Peak | photo_width = | map = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | location = [[Jeollabuk-do]], [[Gyeongsangnam-do]], [[South Korea]] | nearest_city = [[Muju]] | coordinates = {{coords|35.864|127.744|region:KR|notes=<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://protectedplanet.net/sites/Deogyusan_National_Park| title=Deogyusan National Park| work=protectedplanet.net}}</ref>|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|231.65|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref name="knps.or.kr">{{cite web |url=http://english.knps.or.kr/Knp/Deogyusan/Intro/Introduction.aspx?MenuNum=1&Submenu=Npp |title=Deogyusan: Intro |author= |date= |work= |publisher=Korea National Park Service |accessdate=18 September 2010}}</ref> | established = 1 February 1975 | visitation_num = 1 million<ref name="knps.or.kr" /> | visitation_year = | governing_body = Korea National Park Service | world_heritage_site = | url = http://english.knps.or.kr/Knp/Deogyusan/Intro/Introduction.aspx }} {{South Korea national parks}} '''Deogyusan National Park''' ({{lang-ko|'''덕유산국립공원''', '''德裕山國立公園'''}}) is located in the provinces of [[Jeollabuk-do]] and [[Gyeongsangnam-do]], [[South Korea]]. It was designated as the 10th national park in 1975.<ref name="knps.or.kr" /> The park is home to a total of 1,067 plant species, 32 mammal species, 130 bird species, 9 amphibian species, 13 reptile species, 28 fish species, and 1,337 insect species. Endangered animals in the park include [[Flying squirrel]], [[Marten]] and [[Otter]].<ref name="knps.or.kr" />
